== Introduction ==
A plugin for OpenDaylight SAL to be capable of communicating with generic commodity Ethernet switch.
== Release Deliverables ==
{|class="wikitable"
! Name
! Description
|-align="left"
| align="left" | Basic RW
| A plugin with implementation for OpenDaylight SAL API of basic switch reading/writing functions (such as sal.proprogrammer and sal.reader). Switch table could be modified using SNMP.
|-align="left"
| align="left" | Full RW
| A plugin with implementation for OpenDaylight SAL API of switch events listening functions (such as sal.inventory), in addition to Basic RW. Events or status changes of the switch could be received (with SNMP trap) so as to react in the plugin.
|-align="left"
| align="left" | Completed
| A plugin with implementation for all OpenDaylight SAL API (except for the APIs incompatible with generic commodity Ethernet switches), in addition to Rull RW.
|-align="left"
| align="left" | Extended
| A plugin with implementation for extended OpenDaylight SAL API (such as disabling STP and disabling flooding), in addition to Completed.
|}

